The paper deals with the problem of spectrum sensing in cognitive radios, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed method involves the design of a novel analog-to-information converter (AIC), which is a signal processing technique that falls under the category of sparse signal recovery (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of compressed sensing, which is a subfield of signal processing and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the proposed method has potential applications in wireless communication systems (cs.SY).
